Key Match Events: The Cubs took advantage of sloppy defense by the Dodgers to mount a comeback, scoring five times in the eighth inning.
In the Cubs’ 6-3 victory, Shota Imanaga didn’t give up a hit to Shohei Ohtani, Mookie Betts, or Freddie Freeman in seven innings.
The three runs Imanaga surrendered came on solo home runs, two courtesy of Tommy Edman and one from Max Muncy.
